            {
               "text": "### Prerequisites\n\nIn this, we will continue learning about different ways of representing the numbers we use to count. This time, we will get to know the Soroban (算盤), developed in Japan (Nippon koku ou Nihon koku, 日本国).\n\nTo better understand it, we recommend studying the previous text (<htcite0>) before proceeding.",
